# Post-Wick
Social media content on autopilot — engineered for AI citation.
Core loop: URL → AI research → generate 50 posts → swipe approve 
→ autopublish to LinkedIn, X, Instagram, Facebook, TikTok.

## Stack
Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
Auth: Clerk · DB: Neon + Drizzle ORM · Payments: Stripe
AI: Claude API (research + copy) + DALL-E 3 (images)
Research: Jina.ai → Browser Use Cloud fallback
Publishing: LinkedIn API, Twitter/X API, Instagram Graph API

## Key concepts
- Brand: a workspace for one company/website. Users can have 
  multiple brands (agencies). DB table: brands
- Post: a generated social post with platform, content, image,
  status (pending/approved/skipped/published). DB table: posts
- Queue: the swipe approval UI — pending posts waiting for action
- Connection: an OAuth social account linked to a brand. 
  DB table: social_connections

## Rules
- All DB queries go in lib/db/queries/ — never inline in components
- All AI calls go through /api routes — never from client
- Social OAuth tokens are encrypted in DB — never plain text
- All Stripe amounts are in cents — never dollars
- Clerk userId is the source of truth for user identity
- Use server components by default, 'use client' only when needed
- Every async operation needs loading + error + empty states
- Platform limits: LinkedIn 3000 chars, Twitter 280, 
  Instagram 2200, Facebook 63206
